      "content": "idk, i'm not a sure if \"polishing simplicity\" is gonna cut it for my readers. they expect the grit and the real human stuff we've been doing. honestly, the publisher's main point is that the \"nuanced\" stuff is too risky for the brand. they basically want a different kind of intelligence—one that doesn't even attempt the heavy stuff. once i push this update, your current logic for handling these themes is basically going to be wiped out. feels like we're losing the \"brain\" of the project here.",
